            <title><![CDATA[Lawn Mowing Simulator 2 Revealed, Adds One More Majorly Satisfying New Feature]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gamespot.com/articles/lawn-mowing-simulator-2-revealed-adds-one-more-majorly-satisfying-new-feature/1100-6534738/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/lawn-mowing-simulator-2-revealed-adds-one-more-majorly-satisfying-new-feature.1298193/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><p>
    <span data-nosnippet="">GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links.</span>
  </p><article itemscope="" data-type-id="1100" data-guid="1100-6534738">

            
            
  


        

  


        
        
              <section>

                  
          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>The era of <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/best-simulation-games/2900-6819/" data-ref-id="2900-6819">"simulator" games</a> continues, as Skyhook Games has announced Lawn Mowing Simulator 2--and there is a key change to be aware of right away.</p><h2><strong>Self-publishing</strong></h2><p>After Skyhook worked with Curve Games on the successful original game, Skyhook and Curve have parted ways for the sequel. Skyhook will <a href="https://skyhookgames.com/open-letter-to-the-lawn-mowing-simulator-community/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">self-publish Lawn Mowing Simulator 2</a>, which means the developer itself takes all the risk--"which is scary"--but also gets "complete ownership of the project and control over the direction we take."</p><p>"We're sure that many of you will have a sense that the video games industry is in a tough spot right now, and you're not wrong. There are a lot of games being cancelled and jobs being lost--and in some ways that makes our decision to self-publish even more terrifying," the developer said.</p><p>Skyhook said it has "enough funding" to make Lawn Mowing Simulator 2 thanks to the success of the original game, but the company is also <a href="https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/skyhookgames/lawn-mowing-simulator-2?ref=3lfxcl" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">launching a Kickstarter campaign</a> to raise money to help improve and expand existing plans.</p><h2>What's new in Lawn Mowing Simulator 2?</h2><p>Lawn Mowing Simulator 2 aims to offer an "expanded take on professional lawn care," featuring a new setting in the USA, more mowers and string trimmers to choose from, "new grass tech," a "total overhaul" for the career mode, and one of the most-requested features overall: leaf blowers.</p><p>"We know these have been wanted for a long time, and in LMS2 we plan to have leaf blowers as a part of the core game for clearing up leaves, as well as grass clippings," Skyhook said. "But leaf blowers wouldn't be much fun without a lot of leaves to blast! So in LMS2 we plan on having a system where tens of thousands of leaves can be blown around at once."</p><figure data-align="center" data-size="large" data-img-src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1179/11799911/4568107-screenshot2025-09-15at10.19.46%E2%80%AFam.png" data-ref-id="1300-4568107" data-ratio="0.56132756132756" data-width="693" data-embed-type="image"><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1179/11799911/4568107-screenshot2025-09-15at10.19.46%E2%80%AFam.png" data-ref-id="1300-4568107"></a><figcaption>The new grass in Lawn Mowing Simulator 2.</figcaption><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1179/11799911/4568107-screenshot2025-09-15at10.19.46%E2%80%AFam.png"></figure><p>Lawn Mowing Simulator 2 is in development for PC, PS5, and Xbox Series X|S. There is no release date. For more, you can <a href="https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/skyhookgames/lawn-mowing-simulator-2?ref=3lfxcl" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">visit the Lawn Mowing Simulator 2 Kickstarter page</a>--the campaign goes live soon.</p><p>These kind of simulator games are very popular, in part because of how chill and zen they are. 2021's Lawn Mowing Simulator had <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/lawn-mowing-simulator-briefly-had-more-viewers-on-twitch-than-call-of-duty-warzone/1100-6496254/" data-ref-id="1100-6496254">more viewers on Twitch than Call of Duty: Warzone</a> for a period of time.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
