<p dir="ltr">"Vault Hunters! We have heard your feedback on FOV (Field of View) sliders on console," reads the <a href="https://x.com/Borderlands/status/1967001003422871921" rel="nofollow ">post</a>. "The team is currently exploring how to bring these sliders to both Xbox Series X|S and PlayStation 5 versions. We will continue to read your feedback &amp; prioritize game updates with your experience in mind. Thanks all!"</p><p dir="ltr">That obviously isn't an outright confirmation, but it certainly seems likely. Just searching the <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Borderlands/search/?q=fov&amp;cId=cbb16659-b47e-4c0e-9b72-9259fdb0bcbf&amp;iId=b6272bc8-84e1-41e0-b02a-24b613e5ba54" rel="nofollow ">Borderlands subreddit</a> shows you how many people have been asking for FOV options on console, so it seems like a hard request to ignore.</p><p dir="ltr">For more on the game, you can check out GameSpot's <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/borderlands-4-review-too-much-of-an-overcorrection/1900-6418405/">Borderlands 4 review</a>, which found it to be a touch too much of an overcorrection.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
